sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I724005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Elowitz repressilator with added degradation tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Here is simply the standard Elowitz gene with a degradation tag on the reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Susan Westfall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Due to the anolmalous gel results for the I5610 digestion, a new construct of the I5610 was made using I5611 (elowitz repressilator minus the LVA) and the LVA from E0434
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Usage of BsrGI which cleaved the reporter in both the I5611 and E0434 thus putting the two pieces together.
